<subSubSection id="CC6358D1F7D43A4BCA1B84A4DF4555D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="584B60B4779E8F13B26FC875D47F4875" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EDF74463F90CB10E0BEA66161337701A" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">The specific name refers to the type locality; noun in apposition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AF55F81E10D94F7E9E6631FEBCC029C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5D70D231DEA093D6DD25CF4050C67306" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4650C76591FDB6616F7C50E5BD3A009B" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Males can be distinguished from other congeners by the blunt bifurcate embolus tip, two similar components of conductor, and swollen bulb with a notch anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EA4D3D6EBC1A269FE9B30E0CF894E737" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, prolateral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443239" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">13B</figureCitation>
). The females can be distinguished by a pair of angular shaped tubular spermathecae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7CDB943A468144AAD82EBD487A560105" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="185AF8C382A8BE252C934BA4B106C3D1" doi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443239" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" start="Figure 13" startId="F13">
<paragraph id="230E0830703E2C5DA14B40FCB205B0DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B04FEFEB075EE4A2B01F285B9812F8E4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Figure 13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="EA8831BC92EA0F44386AF08A6B910763" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Merizocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merizocera kandy" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandy">
<emphasis id="824E0061295211827F5780F4FD3725D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Merizocera kandy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., holotype male. 
<emphasis id="10C302599B0D7F62444AE193AE36D894" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
Bulb, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="1BFA270F3103E3B574202690F7FDD2B9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">B</emphasis>
bulb, prolateral view 
<emphasis id="EF5AF308A8103A4E431D9682D1ABC152" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">C</emphasis>
palp, prolateral view 
<emphasis id="400F9B6F3205A67F20B3094275DF7DED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D</emphasis>
palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5425CE44247E80274E4F57ED03E32E7B" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="C0CDF308F8620E8C82696A9C0651E991" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC774974246B9D553FFA7B5B2D73E507" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="1681C1CCAF2E01CC0E3F497811173D98" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Male</emphasis>
(holotype). Total length 1.33; carapace 0.63 long, 0.54 wide; abdomen 0.63 long, 0.56 wide. Carapace rounded, brownish, with dark brown marks laterally and dark median stripe on anterior half (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9C7883B0959081D596F165B6D1C2B5B9" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14C</figureCitation>
). Fovea shallow. Thoracic region distinctly elevated medially. Clypeus brownish with dark brown marks medially. Labium dark brown. Sternum dark brown with distinct dark radiating lines. Abdomen ovoid, brownish, with dark brown marks dorsally and ventrally. Legs brown; measurements: I 6.48 (1.70, 0.19, 1.96, 1.76, 0.87), II 4.51 (1.19, 0.20, 1.30, 1.18, 0.64), III 3.66 (0.98, 0.20, 1.05, 0.96, 0.47), IV missing. Palp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F33B19862AAA114193499522BD78C0C6" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, prolateral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443239" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">13A-D</figureCitation>
): femur slender, thrice longer than patella, patella not swollen; tibia swollen, twice wider than and almost similar in length to femur; cymbium with distal protrusion, half as long as femur, length ratio of dorsal elongation and cymbium 0.59; bulb brown, with embolus and conductor arising distally, tegular with a notch anteriorly; embolus bifurcated with blunt tips, two similar components of conductor resemble a C-shape attached adjacent to embolus.
</paragraph>
<caption id="CF0928F7B0BBB245D67DB333C72A1782" doi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" start="Figure 14" startId="F14">
<paragraph id="B06C1FCC6673056A5A798571B08ECF37" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="701C3FBA165DDF459E636F4D187906D6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Figure 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="756D5E49671016208891EAAA33982D1E" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Merizocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merizocera kandy" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandy">
<emphasis id="36D312C1FE99A5D1F7666675A0BA1BDD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Merizocera kandy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. 
<emphasis id="39F87BA5125C17AB37B022C09526CA92" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
Endogyne, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="384F95385CD4973A34542F8D9E7BA49A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">B</emphasis>
female epigastric area, ventral view 
<emphasis id="5634A355E86B5A9EB5A134B08E76126D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">C</emphasis>
male habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="CF26B36A1DE827E834FBD1FE5CEB7F26" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D</emphasis>
female habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="80667B2D6EDF5995A600B3018807F362" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">E</emphasis>
female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="6145F39417919DD77ECBAD7A2B2225F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="CF2E1111C37A42C890A1CDEDDA246C4B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Female</emphasis>
(paratype). General features and colouration similar to those of male (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="196261E7756AF4E59B308EA79D691C9C" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14D, E</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 1.39; carapace 0.65 long, 0.56 wide; abdomen 0.72 long, 0.61 wide. Leg measurements: I missing, II 3.46 (0.90, 0.19, 0.99, 0.85, 0.53), III 2.96 (0.76, 0.19, 0.81, 0.75, 0.45), IV 4.40 (1.10, 0.20, 1.30, 1.14, 0.66). Epigastric area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="76B0DCB79C215899E6BACB0336596B16" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14B</figureCitation>
): elliptical dark brown patch. Endogyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D5A2929A8CE292A09BDEBDE5E92CEAAB" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Merizocera kandy sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443240" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">14A</figureCitation>
) with a pair sloped tubular spermathecae, medially with vertical spiral ducts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5EF4962B56EA68201CB7F9A647BA137" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="10213BE7B7518D8D461204AF03A80E10" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6EC75F6946850BF1F370945A9536994C" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Known only from the type locality (Sri Lanka; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="42A2966A15C894E9C7310A8E0299A13D" captionStart="Figure 52" captionStartId="F52" captionText="Figure 52. Distribution records of the new species of Merizocera from Sri Lanka. 1 M. colombo sp. nov. 2 M. galle sp. nov. 3 M. kandy sp. nov. 4 M. kurunegala sp. nov. 5 M. peraderiya sp. nov. 6 M. ratnapura sp. nov. 7 M. salawa sp. nov. 8 M. thenna sp. nov. 9 M. uva sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443279" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
